Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve, core,
and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into strips) into strips.
Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}(minced). Remove @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from
casing; discard casing.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan over
medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}
(you'll use the rest later). Cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add sausage and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking
water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Once sausage is cooked through, add @diced tomatoes{14%ounce} to pan. Season
with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining Tuscan Heat Spice. Bring to a boil,
then lower heat and let simmer while spaghetti cooks. Once spaghetti is
drained, stir @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 3/4 cup reserved pasta cooking
water (1 cup for 4 servings) into pan. Continue simmering until slightly
reduced, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add spaghetti to pan with sauce; toss to coat. (For 4 servings, carefully
transfer everything into #pot used for pasta.) Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}
(2 TBSP for 4), half the parsley, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}.
Season with salt and pepper. Divide pasta between bowls and sprinkle with
remaining parsley and Parmesan.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time
> until spaghetti is thoroughly coated in sauce.